Sunoco Logistics Partners L.P. Key Developments

Energy Transfer Partners, L.P. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
May 3 17
Energy Transfer Partners, L.P. reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company’s revenues were $6,895 million against $4,481 million a year ago. Operating income was $654 million against $614 million a year ago. Income before income tax expense was $419 million against $318 million a year ago. Net income was $364 million against $376 million a year ago. Net income attributable to partners was $324 million against $311 million a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $1,414 million against $1,412 million a year ago. Distributable cash flow was $934 million against $956 million a year ago. Distributable cash flow attributable to the partners of the company, as adjusted was $859 million against $793 million a year ago. Common unitholders’ interest in net income was $20 million against loss of $67 million a year ago. Basic and diluted net income per share was $0.02 against loss of $0.15 a year ago. Maintenance capital expenditures were $60 million against $59 million a year ago. Capital expenditure was $737 million. Adjusted EBITDA reflects significantly higher results from the midstream and liquids transportation and services segments, offset by lower operating results from the legacy Sunoco Logistics crude oil acquisition and marketing activities.


Sunoco Logistics Partners L.P. has Changed its Name to Energy Transfer Partners, L.P
Apr 28 17
Sunoco Logistics Partners L.P. changed its name to Energy Transfer Partners, L.P.


Sunoco Logistics Partners L.P. will Change its Ticker to ETP from SXL
Apr 28 17
Effective May 01, 2017, Sunoco Logistics Partners L.P. will change its New York Stock Exchange stock ticker symbol to ETP from SXL.


